cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the concept of history independence in data structures, which is relevant to computer security (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), logic and verification (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also provides a recipe for building history independent systems, which further supports the relevance to these sub-categories.
